  "text": "Interactions between learners and other language users in remote locations have opened a new set of opportunities for developing pragmatic competence and exploring intercultural communication [CITATION_1] . Students are paired or placed into groups to work on assigned projects as part of their classroom learning with students at a remote location with whom they inadvertently explore the intricacies of cross-cultural communication [CITATION_2] .",
